  "texts": [
    "Such preprocessing safeguards against the loss of critical information, and prevents the introduction of biases, ensuring that the resulting datasets are representative and reliable for subsequent analysis.",
    "In personalized medicine, treatments and diagnostic tools are customized to an individual genetic profile, requiring precise and tailored preprocessing of genetic data (Duarte and Spencer 2016) to identify unique biomarkers and variations (Tebani et al. 2016).",
    "This process might involve specific SNP (Single Nucleotide Polymorphism) identification algorithms or targeted gene sequencing techniques focusing on particular genome regions relevant to the individual's condition (Chorley et al. 2008).",
    "Similarly, preprocessing techniques must be equally adaptable to cater to the unique features and research goals associated with different fossils.",
    "For instance, preparing SEM images for detailed surface analysis may require distinct algorithms focusing on edge detection and texture enhancement to highlight minute morphological details."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In personalized medicine, treatments and diagnostic tools are customized to an individual genetic profile, requiring precise and tailored preprocessing of genetic data (Duarte and Spencer 2016) to identify unique biomarkers and variations (Tebani et al. 2016).",
    "This process might involve specific SNP (Single Nucleotide Polymorphism) identification algorithms or targeted gene sequencing techniques focusing on particular genome regions relevant to the individual's condition (Chorley et al. 2008)."
